        "goal": "No goal defined.",
        "relevance": "Buffer Overflow: Buffer overflows occur when an application receives more data than its allocated memory can handle, potentially leading to crashes or remote code execution. This test ensures strict bounds checking is enforced on all input fields. Format String Injection: Injecting format string specifiers (e.g., %x, %n) into an application can cause runtime errors, memory disclosure, or code execution. This test verifies that user input is not unsafely passed to formatting functions.",
